{"type":"message","id":"27ef76f6","parentId":"5d0e6957","timestamp":"2026-04-09T22:25:32.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AvS1sUNoRI2dC4jTQI6phukJ","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"memory/2026-04-09.md","content":"### Send Email Skill Details\nThe \"send-email\" skill in OpenClaw is designed to send emails via SMTP using a Python script. Here’s an overview:\n\n**Purpose**: Send emails, including attachments, through an SMTP server with runtime-injected credentials.\n\n**Configuration**: Set up `skills.entries.send-email.env` in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`. Required variables:\n- `EMAIL_SMTP_SERVER`: SMTP server (e.g., `smtp.163.com` for 163.com, `smtp.gmail.com` for Gmail, etc.)\n- `EMAIL_SMTP_PORT`: Port (e.g., `465` for SSL or `587` for TLS)\n- `EMAIL_SENDER`: Email address\n- `EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD`: Authorization code / app-specific password\n\n**Commands**:\n1. Sending plain email:\n   ```bash\n   python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient@example.com\" \"Subject\" \"Body text\"\n   ```\n2. Sending email with attachments:\n   ```bash\n   python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/send-email/send_email.py \"recipient@example.com\" \"Subject\" \"Body text\" \"/path/to/file.pdf\"\n   ```\n\n**Best Practices**:\n- Never manually read configuration files (ensures credentials stay secure). The environment is injected automatically.\n- Use proper SMTP settings relevant to the email provider (e.g., `smtp.gmail.com` for Gmail).\n- Validate the settings if authentication or connection issues arise.\n\nThis skill is highly useful for automated notifications and email-based workflows within OpenClaw."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"github-copilot","model":"gpt-4o","usage":{"input":174,"output":377,"cacheRead":17152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775773525704,"responseId":"chatcmpl-DSs6